result.execSummary:
The defendant Immanuel Smith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must obtain his GED/HSED.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
No consumption or possession of alcohol. No entry into any bars or taverns.
Defendant eligible for expunction upon successful completion of probation.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

timeConds.notes: To be completed within the first year of probation.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Immanuel Smith in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Defendant Immanuel Smith in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:27 AM. Called 16CM127, 16CM154 and 17CF82. Cirilli - all matters resolved as follows: on 17CF82 - joint recommendation that the Court would dismiss count #1 and defendant would plead NC to count #2 and #3 as alleged - 30 days in FC jail on each count - concurrent to each other and concurrent to any sentence he will be receiving on 16CM127 and 16CM154 with a $300.00 fine on each count; on 16CM127 and 16CM154 - joint recommendation of 120 days in FC jail on each count on each case, concurrent to each other and to sentence on 17CF82 with credit of 127 days on 16CM127 and 59 days on 16CM154. State and Smith agree. Court dismisses count #1 on 17CF82. Smith pleads NC to counts #2 and #3 on 17CF82 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty. Cirilli has revocation summary for 16CM127 and 16CM154 and sees no inaccuracies or errors. State - follow joint recommendations as stated by Cirilli previously. Cirilli - follow joint recommendation. Smith makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 17CF82 - counts #2 and #3 - 30 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other and to jail on 16CM127 and 16CM154 - credit for 82 days, $300.00 fine plus costs on each count - 60 days to pay following release from incarceration/CO; on 16CM127 - on both counts - 120 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other and to time on 17CF82 - credit for 127 days for time served; 16CM154 - count #2 - 120 days in FC jail - concurrent to 16CM127 and to 17CF82 - eligible for huber and good time - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - credit for 59 days, turn any unpaid fines into civil judgment, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on August 30, 2017 at 11:00 am.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Immanuel Smith in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 4:09 PM. State - resolved - defendant would plead g/nc to counts #1 and #2 as alleged, DRI counts #3, #4, #5, joint recommendation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 18 months, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: costs on each count, AODA and follow thru, absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns, bars or similar establishments, 100 hours of community service, employment/school. Lynch and Smith agree. Court dismisses and reads in counts #3, #4 and #5. Smith pleads NC to counts #1 and #2 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, find the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Lynch makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - 16 days credit. Smith makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 100 hours of community service - to be completed with in the first 1 year of probation, obtain GED/HSED, costs on each count - paid thru probation, credit for 16 days only if revoked, submit DNA sample with expunction rights given, right to appeal. Lynch asks for expunction under 973.015. Court will allow expunction under 973.015 and explains what that means to the defendant. Adjourned at 4:22 PM.
Final pre-trial on September 14, 2016 at 03:15 pm.
